5","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","before 1490":"before 1490","after 1530":"after 1530","1417":"1417","Pommern, Prussia, Germany":"Pomerania, Prussia, Germany","Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany":"Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany","Pomerania, Prussia":"Pomerania, Prussia, Germany","Pommeren, Germany":"Germany","Pomerania, Prussia, Germany":"Pomerania, Prussia, Germany","Scotland":"Scotland","Germany":"Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Lepel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A male name. Perhaps corrupted from Leopold. Lepel is, however, the name of two towns (New and Old) of Russian Poland, gov. Vitebsk."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margarethe","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margarethe von Lepel was born in 1465, in Pomerania, Prussia, Germany, her father, Heinrich von Lepel, was 40 and her mother, Anna Hanneman, was 48. She married Claus von Kjoller in 1479. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. She died in 1540, in Germany, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1465–1540":"1465–1540","1450–1500":"1450–1500","1480–1530":"1480–1530","1480–1547":"1480–1547","1490–1568":"1490–1568","1500–1584":"1500–1584","1425–1468":"1425–1468","1417–1485":"1417–1485","about 1480":"umbes 1480","Aft 1500":"pärast 1500","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1547":"1547","1425":"1425","1568":"1568","1468":"1468","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1465":"1465","circa 1480":"umbes 1480","Abt. 1500":"umbes 1500","1530":"1530","1485":"1485","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","before 1490":"enne 1490","after 1530":"pärast 1530","1417":"1417","Pommern, Prussia, Germany":"Pommern, Preußen, Saksamaa","Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany":"Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksamaa","Pomerania, Prussia":"Pommern, Preußen, Saksamaa","Pommeren, Germany":"Saksamaa","Pomerania, Prussia, Germany":"Pommern, Preußen, Saksamaa","Scotland":"Scotland","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1465–1540":"1465–1540","1450–1500":"1450–1500","1480–1530":"1480–1530","1480–1547":"1480–1547","1490–1568":"1490–1568","1500–1584":"1500–1584","1425–1468":"1425–1468","1417–1485":"1417–1485","about 1480":"noin 1480",